  "text": "The women believed that culturally specific factors (racism, discrimination, and oppression) can lead to depression. This supports an earlier study conducted by Ward and Heidrich (in press ). Ward and Heidrich used an exploratory descriptive study to examine beliefs about mental illness among 185 African American women. Study results indicated that participants believed racism and discrimination cause depression. Several other investigators have supported these findings, as well [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
